<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="704" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-18"><hi rend="italic">March 18, 1895</hi></date>.
                                (Received March 19.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>My affirmation of the American citizenship of Julio Sanguily having been
                            comprobated and authenticated by the civil government of the Province of
                            Habana, the Governor-General has ordered his transfer from the military
                            to the civil jurisdiction for trial in accordance with protocol twelve
                            January, seventy-seven, as I asked on the 26th ultimo.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>